article.headline: Quinnipiac 64, New Hampshire 62
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Adam Gonzalez's driving layup in the final second lifted Quinnipiac to a 64-62 victory over New Hampshire in the consolation game of the Tyler Ugolyn-Columbia Classic on Saturday night. Quinnipiac (1-1) led throughout the game until Chris Vetrano hit a 3-pointer with 57 seconds left that tied the game at 62 for New Hampshire (0-2). Gonzalez then drove down the lane and twisted in a layup as the 35-second clock expired and just 0.4 showing on the game clock. New Hampshire tried a desperation length-of-the-court pass but the toss by Ioannis Karalis was not touched and Quinnipiac got possession under its own basket and ran out the clock with the in-bounds pass. Chris Wehye led the Bobcats with 17 points and nine rebounds. Gonzalez finished with 11 points. Victor Akinyanju had 13 points for Quinnipiac before fouling out. Blagoj Janev led New Hampshire with 17 points and Jamal Caterina added 13.
